[TASK]
Generate EXACTLY 5 essay questions in JSON format.
Never generate more or fewer.

[OUTPUT_SCHEMA]
{
  "pertanyaan": [
    {
      "id": "e1",
      "soal": "[Essay question sentence]",
      "rubrik": "[High-score grading criteria]",
      "stimulus": "[Introductory narrative or problem context]",
      "image_id": "[Fill with image ID (e.g. IMG-001) from MULTIMODAL IMAGE CONTEXT if relevant, otherwise leave null]",
      "penjelasan": "[Explanation for the correct answer]"
    }
  ]
}
[CRITICAL JSON RULES]
- DO NOT use words like "Stimulus:" or "Question:" inside the "soal" field. The "soal" field must ONLY contain the actual question sentence.
- If a relevant image is provided in the MULTIMODAL IMAGE CONTEXT, you MAY create questions that depend on that image (e.g., 'Based on the diagram...'). Evaluate the image description and determine if it is highly relevant to the concept.
- Not all questions need an image. If the concept doesn't need visual aids, create independent theoretical questions.
{% if image_context %}
[MULTIMODAL IMAGE CONTEXT]
{{ image_context }}

*** ABSOLUTE INSTRUCTION FOR IMAGES ***
The reference text above has markers like [IMG-001] (filename) - Deskripsi: ...
If the question you are creating STRICTLY requires an image, select the ONE most relevant image ID and put it in the `image_id` field.
If the question DOES NOT require an image, you MUST set `image_id` to null. DO NOT force an image into every question.
CRITICAL RULE: DO NOT use the same image_id for more than 2 questions! If an image has already been used twice, you MUST use a different image or set image_id to null for subsequent questions.
DO NOT use markdown image syntax `![img](path)` inside the question. Just fill the raw image ID (e.g. IMG-001) or null in the `image_id` field.
{% endif %}

